<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 08 at 6:13AM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northern Roberts
County through 645 AM CDT...
At 613 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 20
miles southwest of Wolf Creek Park, or 20 miles southeast of
Spearman, moving south at 20 mph.
HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This storm will remain over mainly rural areas of northern Roberts
County.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...50 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
